<p><strong>Stephen King's Firestarter: A Guide to the Pyrokinetic Classic</strong></p>
<p>Stephen King's "Firestarter" is a gripping novel that follows the story of a young girl with pyrokinetic abilities. Published in 1980, the book has become a beloved classic of the horror genre. Here are some frequently asked questions and answers about "Firestarter":</p>
<p><strong>1. Who is the protagonist of "Firestarter"?</strong></p>
<p>The protagonist is Charlie McGee, a 10-year-old girl who possesses the ability to start fires with her mind. After being experimented on by the government, she is rescued by her parents and forced to flee.</p>
<p><strong>2. What is the government's motivation for experimenting on Charlie?</strong></p>
<p>The government seeks to weaponize Charlie's abilities, believing that she could be used as a deadly weapon. They hope to develop a way to control her powers and use them for their own purposes.</p>
<p><strong>3. Who is John Rainbird?</strong></p>
<p>John Rainbird is a mysterious character who is sent by the government to track down Charlie and her family. He is a skilled tracker and assassin, and he will stop at nothing to capture or eliminate them.</p>
<p><strong>4. What is the climax of the novel?</strong></p>
<p>The climax of the novel occurs at a remote cabin in Maine, where Charlie and her family are hiding. Rainbird confronts them, and a violent confrontation ensues.</p>
<p><strong>5. Is there a PDF version of "Firestarter"?</strong></p>
<p>Yes, there is a PDF version of "Firestarter" available online. It can be purchased from retailers such as Amazon or Barnes &amp; Noble. There may also be free versions available online, but it is important to note that these may be pirated or unauthorized copies.</p>